&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parent Infant Mental Health Pathway Lead, Consultant Clinical Psychologist Band 8c: O.6 WTE (22.5 hrs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BWC-Forward Thinking Birmingham 0-25 years Mental Health Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12 months fixed term contract (with the likelihood of renewal)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications for secondment opportunity within BWC or across organisations will be accepted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced qualified senior Clinical Psychologist to develop the FTB Parent Infant Mental Health Pathway. The post holder will be responsible for ensuring the systematic provision of a high quality PIMH (Parent Infant Mental Health) pathway focussed on the 1001 First Days: reaching parents in the perinatal period through to the child’s 2nd birthday The successful candidate for this role will have the experience and drive to lead, develop and support the strategy for a highly specialised PIMH Pathway. Leading the delivery of dedicated supervision, consultation and training as well as specialist PIMH assessments and interventions. Working with partners to increase access to specialist psychological expertise within the early help mental health offer and towards improved joined up delivery through an integrated care system approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be part of the wider Psychological Therapies department within Forward Thinking 0-25 years Mental Health Service and be able to access a range of support and development opportunities to support their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the current commissioning process, this post will initially be appointed to a 12 month fixed term contract with the expectation of renewal in line with the usual recruitment procedure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Dr Ashley-Christopher Fallon, Head of Psychological Therapies, via ashley-christopher.fallon@nhs.net . Mobile 07812260710 or landline 0121 333 9999.&lt;/p&gt;
